# NOT GROUPED AND SORTED BY SENTIMENT (Ascending, so neg -> positive)
# note that ties are not broken by any meaningful measure, and therefore reflects the
# "implementation detail" of the data structure: in this case, it is the order of data being added (so,
# the order of the data being read from the file) but both the order of read, and the order of adding to the list
# would be considered UNRELIABLE things. It's deterministic, but for example in a different version of python
# this might change, and any code using this should nto rely on any particular ordering besides
# the sentiment score.

for r in sorted(DDD_text_responses_list_filtered, key=lambda x : x["sentiment"]["compound"]):
    print(round(r["sentiment"]["compound"], 2), "\t", r["response"])
